laboratory_examinations.findings: Normal cell counts, normal protein and glucose levels; no organisms evident on Gram’s or acid-fast bacilli staining.
Generalized theta-range background slowing; no epileptiform activity.
Showed generalized brain atrophy, characterized by more prominent changes in the left frontal lobe and asymmetric hyperintensity in occipitoparietal and posterior temporal subcortical white matter.
Alkaline phosphatase level was 130 U/L (slightly above normal range), AST level was 54 U/L (above normal range), and ALT level was 67 U/L (above normal range).

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Plasma Testing for Very-Long-Chain Fatty Acids
laboratory_examinations.findings: C26:0 was 2.86 µmol/L (not normal). Ratio of C24:0 to C22:0 was 1.50 (not normal).
